  "commentary": "With SPX at 6599.96 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-16.1B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+23.1B), dealers are likely buying this dip given we're below the key 6605 resistance level where they'd typically sell rallies. The PIN regime with massive 23.9B total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting forces, with the 6590-6605 range acting as a critical pivot zone where dealer flow switches from amplifying (below 6590) to stabilizing (above 6605). Watch for rejection at 6605 if we rally, or potential acceleration if we break below 6590 support.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy trading between 6590-6605 with dealers acting as a stabilizer.",
